                            <comment id="485459" author="courrier" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2026 13:19:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nangelinas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nangelinas&quot;&gt;nangelinas&lt;/a&gt; what do you think about this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After discussion this with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eaujames&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eaujames&quot;&gt;eaujames&lt;/a&gt;, adding the dirty flag may be a bit complex since there is a possible race between the copytool&apos;s responses. If the error arrives before the success, then the file will not have the archived flag. Maybe looking at inflight HSM requests in the request hash table would make it possible to solve this race? If we have an error and at least one inflight archive, we should add the dirty flag. But then how do we detect that the file should stay dirty when the successful archive arrives. I don&apos;t think this could work in practice unfortunately...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe the solution is to allow multiple archives for a single FID but prevent multiple inflight archives. This should be solvable by doing an hashtable lookup before sending the HSM requests which should scale better than the original deduplication.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
